@Vinod, Its probably not  different but that argument is for another day :).

For the AM getting KILL signal, we can never be sure that the AM will call finishapplicationMaster. How would you enforce that? I dont think we can get away from not sending kill to the RM at *all* times. I dont think we can rely on AM to be responsive and do the right work. Thoughts?

On the renaming of the finishAPplication, I do agree we should change that.
